	<div class="page" id="page-discord">
		<form action="/config/discord" method="post">
			<div class="panel">
				{{> panelHeader title="Setup Information" }}
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						If you have a Discord server and would like to use commands to add records to the database, as
						well as receive notifications for errors and warnings, you can set up a bot to send and listen
						for new messages.
					</p>
					<p>
						To start, make sure you have your own Discord Bot, by visiting the
						<a href="https://discord.com/developers/applications" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
							<strong>Discord Developer dashboard {{> svgExternal}}</strong>
						</a>, and set up a bot with the ability to <em>read, send, and delete message content</em>.
						Then, invite this bot to your private server.
					</p>
					<hr>
					<p>
						Adding a Discord bot to your server will listen for these commands. They are detected if sent as
						regular messages.
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>
							<p><code>youtube &lt;URL&gt; [optional date/time, ISO8601 format]</code></p>
							<p>
								Adds a YouTube video to your list of "liked youtube videos". If you provide a date/time,
								it will be logged using that date/time, otherwise it will use the current date/time.
							</p>
							<p>
								<em>Example:</em>
								<small><code>youtube https://youtu.be/5G3M9WDK_eI</code></small>
							</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<p><code>bookmark &lt;URL&gt; &lt;TITLE&gt;</code></p>
							<p>Adds the following to your saved bookmarks, using the provided title.</p>
							<p>
								<em>Example:</em>
								<small><code>bookmark https://floof.fm moonfloof</code></small>
							</p>
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="panel">
				{{> panelHeader title="Settings" }}
				<div class="content">
					<section>
						<p><strong>Bot Token</strong></p>
						<p class="description">
							To get an access token, visit the Developer dashboard linked above, and copy the Token from
							the "Bot" page.
						</p>
						<p class="description">💭 Leave this field blank to disable any use of Discord.</p>
						<input type="text" class="right" name="discordToken" id="discordToken"
							value="{{config.discord.token}}" placeholder="Discord Bot Token" />
					</section>
					<hr>

					<section>
						<p><strong>Command Channel ID</strong></p>
						<p class="description">
							Once the bot is in your server, it will only listen to commands sent to this channel. To get
							the channel ID, go to your Discord settings, enable Developer Mode, then right-click the
							channel you want to use and click "<em>Copy Channel ID</em>".
						</p>
						<input type="text" class="right" name="discordChannelId" id="discordChannelId"
							value="{{config.discord.channelId}}" placeholder="Discord Command Channel ID" />
					</section>
				</div>
			</div>

			{{> internal/configSaveChanges}}
		</form>
	</div>

	<div class="page" id="page-google">
		<form action="/config/google" method="post">
			<div class="panel">
				{{> panelHeader title="Setup Information" }}
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						Google's APIs are used for getting YouTube video details (i.e. channel name, video title, and
						duration) and searching for map places for check-ins.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="panel">
				{{> panelHeader title="Settings" }}
				<div class="content">
					<section>
						<p><strong>API Key</strong></p>
						<p class="description">
							To get an API key, load up the
							<a href="https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
								<strong>Google Cloud API Credentials {{> svgExternal}}</strong>
							</a> page, create a new API key, and make sure to restrict it to the
							<em>YouTube Data API v3</em> API and, if you want to use Google Maps to search for check-in
							locations, the <em>Places API</em> too.
						</p>
						<p class="description">💭 If you leave this blank, the Google APIs will not be used.</p>
						<input type="text" class="right" name="googleApiKey" id="googleApiKey"
							value="{{config.google.apiKey}}" placeholder="API Read Access Token" />
					</section>
					<hr>

					<section>
						<input type="checkbox" name="googlePlacesApiEnabled" id="googlePlacesApiEnabled" {{#if
							config.google.placesApiEnabled}}checked="checked" {{/if}} />
						<label for="googlePlacesApiEnabled"><strong>Enable the Places API</strong></label>
						<p class="description">
							For checking in, you can use the Places API. However, the use of this API
							<strong>requires a billing account and you may be charged.</strong> If you do not have a
							billing account associated with your Google Console account, the Places API will not work.
						</p>
					</section>
					<hr>

					<section>
						<p><strong>Places API: Ignored Search Categories</strong></p>
						<p class="description">
